[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating metadata generation**\n\nI think the project named Forge manages metadata generation outside of the agent, but I wonder why tests would fail under native conditions. Wait, does that mean no metadata rules apply? So, Forge generates metadata externally? The current metadata lacks an Object constructor, but if the test passes on the JVM, does that mean the agent could generate metadata? Also, I can't modify it. The dynamic-access coverage seems to come from the JVM's test runs, which might explain why the report is outdated.\n\n**Investigating serialization issue**\n\nI'm thinking about how ObjectOutputStream.writeObject is used in BCPicnicPrivateKey.writeObject and if it's being invoked reflectively through ObjectStreamClass. It's possible that coverage may not detect it since the call is via reflection. But the bytecode in the method does include the call. I wonder if the actual BCPicnicPrivateKey class in the artifact is not serializable... but according to my understanding, it is. Hmm, maybe I should use javap to check?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_087a0585f0914064016a26545b21a88195b219d4d3109ab899\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJlRwFfYDV7vM_91HC9UoMAi4y4cfDLYNDDIWyoVZRmaugR7tLdU6pfEB_17Y59bC5nmbzTJq7LY1bb4krnvnlrNtq-XpjzLOkz810PiP1dSxG7XpQlxAocfJOvZLVdoqUQQFdPZsWUVq3hcyHR8zLEd0gDE-xotKAUrHTROWATGvcH55y4RRyyIyBFzG6s_yebVI8YxpaMg7LG8-kzii9LIep_xLNZRQg52mDqycYwt7bVXhyynx2alRwRRf85oFrqpRxHxQXtlyy38zMXO15Xl_YubqXUH_kKixDL7zVUvMkJP6aVVYlGiCqAYmXqfp1K1oNwpcrh8fO12vkSJwRDlObSdAd0JKsefXE2IoJw_p8TGJ0t1FfS0uXXszryF4OP81U8BO2rl9oWSidwSkUv9sxFVw6blVQg8IEmbKbOpCx2x1xmvSaY1FHIHcBpgcnSfwXmoNpgt5EK00VF0ZiQNRYNQpMcLo1MSqpRg_atPJN8my6wAK3XP03XfEvRFaW173QSBK0foQ3sGhEBLwgbDa3A6mO0O0usStsP2nByCFIs6JCry_28Bf5vEzw4qBurlr7gieoFfLE0UuKWgydVn2qfpE0DxbXOK83OaJY0OKQD37JKhNy0xL7OOXjCmc5uPDoQdad3409eFXU5gf6E8oS2evBPWSeDO_pEO2iK